# JSON Content Guidelines

## Memory Entry Format
Each memory entry in [memories.json](mdc:src/content/memories.json) must follow this structure:
```json
{
    "title": "string",
    "date": "YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ssZ"
}
```

## Validation Rules
1. Title must be a non-empty string
2. Date must be a valid ISO 8601 timestamp
3. No additional properties are allowed
4. No comments in JSON files
5. Use 4-space indentation
6. Use double quotes for strings
7. No trailing commas in JSON

## Common Issues to Avoid
1. Invalid date formats
2. Missing required fields
3. Extra whitespace or formatting inconsistencies
4. Using single quotes instead of double quotes
5. Adding comments (use external documentation instead)

## Example Valid Entry
```json
{
    "title": "Team Building Event",
    "date": "2024-03-20T14:30:00Z"
}
```
